name: Will Juergens - What if you died soon?

metadata.description: For real. What if you did? Not saying you should want to - but what if you did? I think about death a lot. I'm a bit of an Edward Allen Hoe. Helps me live a vibrant life to have a goth colored mind. This tune is danceable but sombering. Kinda country kinda folk kinda electronic. You could dance around a fire to this I think. I hope you enjoy and I hope it helps you live with death.

lyrics.text:
I’ll be around in use. 
Soon.
The hem of my jeans is sprouting roots.
I’m picking a flower for you.

Look at a face.
What does it think?
Is it making time for you?
What if you died soon?

What if I died?
Go ahead and take my spot in traffic.
You just might kill me.
Maybe you’ll raise me
up out in another loop.
Maybe I’ll raise you too.

Look at a face.
What does it think?
Is it making time for you?
Look at my face.
What does it say?
Is it making time?
What if you die soon?
